!! Article II: The Executive

!!! II.a. The Executive Hierarchy and Election
    
    The President of the United States shall lead the Executive Branch with
    the assistance of a Vice President and their Cabinet.

    The President, Vice President, and the four named members of the Cabinet
    --- the Secretary of State, Secretary of Defense, Secretary of the Treasury,
    and Attorney General --- shall be elected every $4$ years.  

    No person may serve as President for more than one full term. 

!!! II.b. The President
!!! II.c. The Vice President
!!! II.d. The Cabinet
!!!! II.d.0. Membership and Appointment 

    The Executive's Cabinet shall consist of
        a Secretary of State,
        a Secretary of Defense,
        a Secretary of the Treasury,
        an Attorney General,
        a Secretary of Homeland Security,
        a Secretary of the Interior,
        a Secretary of Commerce,
    and a number of department heads as the Congress may by law provide.

